CueBright © James Tattersall 2017 Version 1.0.1 (first release)
This application allows the LEDs of a CUE (Corsair Utility Engine) compatible keyboard to be overridden. To do this, both this application and Corsair Utility Engine must be kept open.
Syntax: [hex color (#xxxxxx)] [brightness (0.0-1.0)]
Unfortunately I am not able to modify or fetch the current configuration of the keyboard, so currently the entire keyboard can only be set to a single color.
